Text.string: I have something for you, Vault Hunter.
Could you check on a friend of mine?

Oh, shut up! You're not gonna explode! Probably, no promises. I'm getting better at this, really! Besides, if you didn't want to be horribly experimented on, you should've joined the family! Honestly, this is on you, man.
Vercuvio... gone. He taught me how to cheat at dice. What I wouldn't give to feed Troy Calypso to Korilax the Invincible—and Korilax owes me one! Keep searching for the others.

Gonna try chargin' up one of my followers soon. Maybe it'll work better with a willing subject. Just gotta come up with a name for my crew...||Troy-Boys? No, blegh.||Supercharged Glowing Mega-Badass—eh, that's too long.||Anointed? Boom, God-King Troy's Anointed. Nailed it.
His name was Beckett. Scoundrel, bank robber, friend. Only Dean remains. Surely he is lost, too...
Oooohohohoh, HOT DAMN! My first Anointed! Who wants to fight him? Huh?! You, you, and... you!
[screams]
W-What is that thing?
That's Dean's voice... At least find his remains, Vault Hunter. That is the least he deserves.
Help!
Can anyone hear me?!
I don't wanna die like this!
Help! HELP!

While incarcerated by the Children of the Vault, I joined a gang! For protection as well as camaraderie. Good fellows. Freedom fighters and ruthless criminals, and often both! If you would kindly check up on them, I would be most grateful. You can find them at the prison.
Dean! He's alive! Vault Hunter, you must free him!
W-Who... are you?
Easy. Dean, right? Hammerlock sent me.
Calm yourself. Dean, yes? Hammerlock sent me.
Relax, friend. You are Dean, yes? Hammerlock sent me.
Relax, boyo. You Dean? Hammerlock sent me.
Hammerlock... yeah, I knew... I knew a Hammerlock. Talked funny. He... he sent you to rescue me? Oh, good.
Oh no... it's back. It's BACK!
Kill it!
You... You did it. You killed that thing.
Thanks. The others're all dead. Just dumb luck I was spared. I was losing hope, getting ready to, you know... Well. You know.
This gun, it's for you. If you ever see that Troy dude, blow his damn brains out, yeah? Yeah.
My gangmates got me through some dark times indeed. The last time I saw them was before I was dragged away for my interrogation, but I remain hopeful that they escaped.
Watch out, Vault Hunter!
That fiend was playing dead! Defend yourself.
Thank goodness Dean survived. Now we can continue our crochet and shank-making lessons. Remarkably similar skill sets, you know.
Why, that's Jensen's... oh dear...
Jensen, my captive bud. Gonna try a little experiment on you. On a scale of “bad” to “kill me”, how's this feel?
Hnnnrghrrgh!
Oh, MAN! Splash zone! Watch out! Ha! This Eridium stuff is the TITS! Oh! On to the next heretic!
Troy Calypso was experimenting on his prisoners... and my dear friend was his victim. Jensen had the voice of an angel, and his toilet wine was divine! Vault Hunter, you must find the others!
No! No, please! I don't wanna explode!
